f  what is the most important thing we can think about at this extraordinary moment.', 154, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (420151, 'Fill the unforgiving minute with sixty seconds worth of distance run.', 843, 0), (420152, 'The present moment is creative  creating with an unheard-of intensity.', 60507, 0), (420153, 'The only way to live is to accept each minute as an unrepeatable miracle  which is exactly what it is: a miracle and unrepeatable.', 20188, 0), (420154, 'Who makes quick use of the moment is a genius of prudence.', 23209, 0), (420155, 'I live now and only now  and I will do what I want to do this moment and not what I decided was best for me yesterday.', 9901, 0), (420156, 'But what minutes! Count them by sensation  and not by calendars  and each moment is a day.', 1827, 0), (420157, 'It may be life is only worthwhile at moments. Perhaps that is all we ought to expect.', 12805, 0), (420158, 'To finish the moment  to find the journey''s end in every step of the road  to live the greatest number of good hours  is wisdom.', 760, 0), (420159, 'Our latest moment is always our supreme moment. Five minutes delay in dinner now is more important than a great sorrow ten years gone.', 4111, 0), (420160, 'God speaks to all individuals through what happens to them moment by moment.', 64042, 0), (420161, 'Be always resolute with the present hour. Every moment is of infinite value.', 62224, 0), (420162, 'A player''s effectiveness is directly related to his ability to be right there  doing that thing  in the moment. ... He can''t be worrying about the past or the future or the crowd or some other extraneous event. He must be able to respond in the here and now.', 65991, 0), (420163, 'We inhabit ourselves without valuing ourselves  unable to see that here  now  this very moment is sacred  but once it''s gone-its value is incontestable.', 852, 0), (420164, 'Life is all memory except for the one present moment that goes by so quick you can hardly catch it going.', 355, 0), (420165, 'The trouble is not that we are never happy-it is that 