n works with strangeness upon the body of time. An hour  once it lodges in the queer element of the human spirit  may be stretched to fifty or a hundred times its clock length  on the other hand  an hour may be accurately represented by the timepiece of the mind by one second.', 113, 0), (420243, 'When you have a great and difficult task  something perhaps almost impossible  if you only work a little at a time  every day a little  suddenly the work will finish itself.', 19178, 0), (420244, 'Champions know there are no shortcuts to the top. They climb the mountain one step at a time. They have no use for helicopters!', 65999, 0), (420245, 'The world doesn''t come to the clever folks  it comes to the stubborn  obstinate  one-idea-at-a-time people.', 16076, 0), (420246, 'One of the greatest evils of the day among those outside of prison is their sense of futility. Young people say  What is the sense of our small effort? They cannot see that we must lay one brick at a time  take one step at a time  we can be responsible only for the one action of the present moment.', 848, 0), (420247, 'One only gets to the top rung of the ladder by steadily climbing up one at a time  and suddenly all sorts of powers  all sorts of abilities which you thought never belonged to you- suddenly become within your own possibility and you think  "Well  I''ll have a go  too."', 1945, 0), (420248, 'Nothing is particularly hard if you divide it into small jobs.', 1796, 0), (420249, 'Let no one be deluded that a knowledge of the path can substitute for putting one foot in front of the other.', 64449, 0), (420250, 'Look at a stone cutter hammering away at his rock  perhaps a hundred times without as much as a crack showing in it. Yet at the hundred-and-first blow it will split in two  and I know it was not the last blow that did it  but all that had gone before.', 21350, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (420251, 'Home wasn''t built in a day.', 64697, 0), (420252, 'Happiness is a tide: it carries you only a little way at a time  but you have covered a vast space before you know that you are moving at all.', 62350, 0), (420253, 'Not to go back is somewhat to advance. And men must walk  at least  before they dance.', 3348, 0), (420254, 'Great things are not done by impulse  but by a series of small things brought together.', 89, 0), (420255, 'Well-being is attained little by little  and is no little thing itself.', 64208, 0), (420256, 'Bigness comes from doing many small things well. ... Individually  they are not very dramatic transactions. Together  though  they add up.', 66000, 0), (420257, 'If you only keep adding little by little  it will soon become a big heap.', 3287, 0), (420258, 'He who would learn to fly one day must first learn to stand and walk and run and climb and dance  one cannot fly into flying.', 11, 0), (420259, 'All that I have accomplished ... has been by that plodding  patient  persevering process of accretion which builds the ant heap particle by particle  thought by thought  fact by fact.', 66001, 0), (420260, 'If we take care of the moments  the years will take care of themselves.', 20818, 0), (420261, 'Many things which cannot be overcome when they are together  yield themselves up when taken little by little.', 4891, 0), (420262, 'True worth is doing each day some little good  not dreaming of great things to do by and by.', 33, 0), (420263, 'Little by little does the trick.', 1733, 0), (420264, 'It is by attempting to reach the top at a single leap that so much misery is caused in the world.', 65231, 0), (420265, 'Yesterday I dared to struggle. Today I dare to win.', 63078, 0), (420266, 'I think and think for months  for years. Ninety-nine times the conclusion is false. The hundredth time I am right.', 104, 0), (420267, 'Many strokes overthrow the tallest oaks.', 56653, 0), (420268, '