INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (420301, 'Human felicity is produced not so much by great pieces of good fortune that seldom happen as by little advantages that occur every day.', 1077, 0), (420302, 'The mere sense of living is joy enough.', 91, 0), (420303, 'Trifles make up the happiness or the misery of mortal life.', 13963, 0), (420304, 'Even a small star shines in the darkness.', 63192, 0), (420305, 'How far that little candle throws his beams! So shines a good deed in a naughty world.', 13, 0), (420306, 'It is better to light a candle than to curse the darkness.', 7652, 0), (420307, 'If you don''t enjoy getting up and working and finishing your work and sitting down to a meal with family or friends  then the chances are you''re not going to be happy. If someone bases his happiness or unhappiness on major events like a great new job  huge amounts of money  a flawlessly happy marriage or a trip to Paris  that person isn''t going to be happy much of the time. If  on the other hand  happiness depends on a good breakfast  flowers in the yard  a drink or a nap  then we are more likely to live with quite a bit of happiness.', 1350, 0), (420308, 'The big things that come our way are ... the fruit of seeds planted in the daily routine of our work.', 5249, 0), (420309, 'The little things are infinitely the most important.', 64169, 0), (420310, 'Enjoy the little things  for one day you may look back and realize they were the big things.', 1321, 0), (420311, 'It is in trifles  and when he is off his guard  that a man best shows his character.', 1304, 0), (420312, 'Life is denied by lack of attention  whether it be to cleaning windows or trying to write a masterpiece.', 44758, 0), (420313, 'It was only a sunny smile  But it scattered the night And little it cost in the giving  Like morning light  And made the day worth living.', 33, 0), (420314, 'Sometimes the littlest things in life are the hardest to take. You can sit on a mountain more comfortably than on a tack.', 33, 0), (420315, 'Put your heart  mind  intellect  and soul even to your smallest acts. This is the secret of success.', 62960, 0), (420316, 'The smallest effort is not lost  Each wavelet on the ocean tost Aids in the ebb-tide or the flow  Each rain-drop makes some floweret blow  Each struggle lessens human woe.', 54927, 0), (420317, 'In life''s small things be resolute and great To keep thy muscle trained  Know''st thou when Fate Thy measure takes  or when she''ll say to thee  "I find thee worthy  do this deed for me?"', 1247, 0), (420318, 'He that is faithful in that which is least is faithful also in much  and he that is unjust in the least is unjust also in much.', 5587, 0), (420319, 'We think in generalities  but we live in detail.', 2606, 0), (420320, 'I cannot do everything  but still I can do something  and because I cannot do everything  I will not refuse to do something that I can do.', 31769, 0), (420321, 'I am convinced that there are times in everybody''s experience when there is so much to be done  that the only way to do it is to sit down and do nothing.', 6518, 0), (420322, 'We cannot do everything at once  but we can do something at once.', 4110, 0), (420323, 'You have to accept whatever comes and the only important thing is that you meet it with the best you have to give.', 141, 0), (420324, 'Nobody makes a greater mistake than he who did nothing because he could only do a little.', 2026, 0), (420325, 'We must not... ignore the small daily differences we can make which  over time  add up to big differences that we often cannot foresee.', 7224, 0), (420326, 'A terrace nine stories high begins with a pile of earth.', 15, 0), (420327, 'Not all things are blest  but the seeds of all things are blest.', 1736, 0), (420328, 'God requires a faithful fulfillment of the merest trifle given us to do  rather than the most ardent aspiration to things to which we are not called.', 63291, 0), (420329, 'Large streams from little mountains flow