INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (421001, 'We can have democracy in this country or we can have great wealth concentrated in the hands of a few  but we can''t have both.', 16727, 0), (421002, 'I am opposed to millionaires  but it would be dangerous to offer me the position.', 286, 0), (421003, 'Sleep  riches and health to be truly enjoyed must be interrupted.', 62442, 0), (421004, 'The wealth of a nation consists not in its mass of material things  but in its system. The natural resources of South America are not inferior to those of the United States  but the wealth of the two regions is vastly different. The land of India is far richer than that of Japan  but the comparative wealth of the two nations is reversed.', 62813, 0), (421005, 'I have enough money to get by. I''m not independently wealthy  just independently lazy  I suppose.', 66075, 0), (421006, 'I have no complex about wealth. I have worked hard for my money  producing things people need. I believe that the able industrial leader who creates wealth and employment is more worthy of historical notice than politicians or soldiers.', 62806, 0), (421007, 'I was born into it and there was nothing I could do about it. It was there  like air or food  or any other element. The only question with wealth is what you do with it.', 11161, 0), (421008, 'Riches do not consist in the possession of treasures  but in the use made of them.', 1702, 0), (421009, 'I wish to become rich  so that I can instruct the people and glorify honest poverty a little  like those kind-hearted  fat  benevolent people do.', 286, 0), (421010, 'In big houses in which things are done properly  there is always the religious element. The diurnal cycle is observed with more feeling when there are servants to do the work.', 6481, 0), (421011, 'True abundance is not about gathering more things  it''s about touching the place in us that is connected to the divine source of abundance  so that we know what we need in the moment will be provided.', 1055, 0), (421012, 'It''s time we put thoughts of lack behind us. It''s time for us to discover the secrets of the stars  to sail to an uncharted land  to open up a new heaven where our spirits can soar.', 7175, 0), (421013, 'It is good to have things that money can buy  but it is also good to check up once in awhile and be sure we have the things money can''t buy.', 23136, 0), (421014, 'Ordinary riches can be stolen  real riches cannot. In your soul are infinitely precious things that cannot be taken from you.', 40, 0), (421015, '''Let us not get so busy or live so fast that we can''t listen to the music of the meadow or the symphony that glorifies the forest. Some things in the world are far more important than wealth  one of them is the ability to enjoy simple things.', 1005, 0), (421016, 'It is wealth to be content.', 15, 0), (421017, 'Who is rich? He that rejoices in his portion.', 1077, 0), (421018, 'If you''re happy  you''re wealthy! Happiness doesn''t need a bank account.', 64549, 0), (421019, 'Wealth ... is a relative thing since he that has little and wants less is richer than he that has much but wants more.', 432, 0), (421020, 'Sometimes when you have everything  you can''t really tell what matters.', 66076, 0), (421021, 'The only question with wealth is what you do with it.', 11161, 0), (421022, 'The rich man is not one who is in possession of much  but one who gives much.', 65030, 0), (421023, 'Having given all he had  He then is very rich indeed.', 15, 0), (421024, 'If you see yourself as prosperous  you will be. If you see yourself as continually hard up  that is exactly what you will be.', 10101, 0), (421025, 'Prosperity is just around the corner.', 7777, 0), (421026, 'Wealth is not his that has it  but his who enjoys it.', 1077, 0), (421027, 'I have mental joys and mental health  Mental friends and mental wealth  I''ve a wife that I love and that loves me  I''ve all but riches bodily.', 221, 0), (421028, 'Surplus wealth is a sacred trust which its possessor is bound to administer in his life-time for the good of the community.', 4963, 0), (421029, 'If you would be wealthy  think of saving as well as of getting.', 1077, 0), (421030, 'The ideal social state is not that in which each gets an equal amount of wealth  but in which each gets in proportion to his contribution to the general stock.', 40782, 0), (421031, 'I''ll fares the land  to hastening ills a prey  Where wealth accumulates  and men decay  Princes and Lords may flourish  or may fade -  A breath can make them  as a breath has made -  But a bold peasantry  their country''s pride  When once destroy''d can never be supplied.', 2204, 0), (421032, 'Riches either serve or govern the possessor.', 2542, 0), (421033, 'The wealth of nations is men  not silk and cotton and gold.', 63576, 0), (421034, 'Life is short. The sooner that a man begins to enjoy his wealth the better.', 2087, 0), (421035, 'Our Lord commonly giveth Riches to such gross asses  to whom he affordeth nothing else that is good.', 1746, 0), (421036, 'It is easier for a camel to go through the eye of a needle  than for a rich man to enter into the kingdom of God.', 21732, 0), (421037, 'I am rich beyond the dreams of avarice.', 65495, 0), (421038, 'All wealth is the product of labor', 2375, 0), (421039, 'Get place and wealth  if possible  with grace  If not  by any means get wealth and place.', 3348, 0), (421040, 'Riches certainly make themselves wings.', 44178, 0), (421041, 'He that maketh haste to be rich shall not be innocent.', 44178, 0), (421042, 'He heapeth up riches  and knoweth not who shall gather them.', 5587, 0), (421043, 'No good man ever became suddenly rich.', 62420, 0), (421044, 'Can snore upon the flint  when resty sloth Finds the down pillow hard.', 13, 0), (421045, 'One of the most adventurous things left is to go to bed  for no one can lay a hand on our dreams.', 64212, 0), (421046, 'Sleeping is no mean art. For its sake one must stay awake all day.', 11,